en: Plato thought that three conditions must be met in order for us to “ know ” something : the notion in question must actually be true ; we must believe it ( because if we do not believe something that is true , we can hardly claim that we know it ) ; and , most subtly , it must be justifiable – there must be reasons why we believe the notion to be true .
